Package com.apple.audio.units

Interface Summary
AUPropertyListener Classes implement this interface to receive notifications of changes in properties of an AudioUnit
AURenderCallback This is a callback that an app can register with an AudioUnit to both gain notifications before and after a renderSlice is called on an audio unit (AudioUnit.installRenderNotification) and also as a replacement for providing input to a unit directly through this callback (AudioUnit.setInputCallback).
 

Class Summary
AUComponent  
AUConstants This class contains the general constants defined for use with AudioUnits
AudioDeviceOutputUnit This class represents those audio units that talk directly to an output device on the System.
AudioUnit AudioUnits represent opened components that perform some transformational actions on Audio data.
AudioUnitConnection Used to contain information about the connection of an AudioUnit to some destination.
AUParameterInfo Used to retrieve information about the general parameter values of the AudioUnit
AUProperties These are property identifiers for Audio Units.
MusicDevice The MusicDevice class typically represents a Software Synthesiser.
OutputAudioUnit This class represents those audio units that talk directly to an output device on the System.
